nolink "false"

\end_inset

 shows a discontinuous shifted sign function defined as:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f(x)=\begin{cases}
-1 & \text{if }x<-0.5\\
0 & \text{if }x=-0.5\\
1 & \text{if }x>-0.5
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

We can observe that the accuracy of the quadrature approximation is even lower than for the previous non-smooth function,
 and the error fluctuates significantly depending on whether an odd or even number of nodes and weights is used.
 This occurs because 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x)$
\end_inset

 is discontinuous within the interval 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 (specifically at 
\begin_inset Formula $x=-0.5$
\end_inset

).
 We could again split the interval 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 into subintervals (e.g.,
 at the point of discontinuity) to achieve a more accurate result.
 In this case,
 a one-point quadrature rule applied to each of the two subintervals would be sufficient to obtain the exact value of the integral.
 
