\]

\end_inset

and an inner product
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left\langle \left[F\right],\left[G\right]\right\rangle _{L^{2}}\coloneqq\lim_{i\rightarrow\infty}\intop_{I}f_{i}\left(x\right)g_{i}\left(x\right)dx.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Corollary
\begin_inset Formula $L^{2}(I)$
\end_inset

 is a Hilbert space.
 Also,
 this definition of 
\begin_inset Formula $L^{2}(I)$
\end_inset

 space yields the same space (isometrically isomorphic) as 
\begin_inset Formula $L^{2}(I)$
\end_inset

 under Lebesgue measure 
